    "title": "Add blind signing support for schnorr",
    "body": "21:33 @gmaxwell signer with pubkey P generates k, sends R = kG  to user.  User computes blinding factors a,b   computes R' = R + aG + bP  ; e' = H(R' || M) - b  sends e' to signer, signer computes s' = k + e'x; user computes s = s' + a, signature is r',s. \n\n(I derived that myself, it looks right to me-- anyone have a citation for that protocol?)\n\nLooks like an implementation could also easily support multisig blindsigning as well.\n",
